creator: Irvin S. Cobb
description:
LibriVox recording of Cobb's Anatomy by Irvin S. Cobb.
Read in English by Phil Chenevert
Irving S. Cobb discusses the human body and it's various strange parts in his own inimitable hilarious style. He discusses the tummy and the problems of having a large one; teeth, hair and finally hands and feet. Summary by Phil Chenevert
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
